{
  "texts": [
    "More formally, for each pair (𝑤, 𝐴) ∈ D, E includes a pair (𝑇 (𝑤), 𝐴).",
    "Note that, since E is a set, there is only one occurrence for each pair (𝑇 (𝑤), 𝐴).",
    "We also remove from E all the examples sharing the same textual description 𝑇 (𝑤) but associated with different labels.",
    "Indeed, such examples represent patterns shared by multiple activities, and considering these as additional information may be misleading for the LLM.",
    "Semantic-based Example Selection.In principle, we may include the whole set E in each user prompt as additional context for ADL-LLM."
  ]
}